atlasmind.specialistRoutingOverrides.markdownDescription:
Per-domain overrides for specialist routing automation. Supported top-level keys today are `media-generation`, `visual-analysis`, `voice`, `research`, `robotics`, and `simulation`. Each domain entry can disable the route, pin a `preferredProvider`, override `budget` or `speed`, tighten `requiredCapabilities`, or swap the fallback `commandId` used for dedicated workflow surfaces.

Example:
```json
{
  "research": {
    "preferredProvider": "perplexity",
    "budget": "expensive"
  },
  "visual-analysis": {
    "preferredProvider": "openai",
    "requiredCapabilities": ["vision"]
  }
}
```

AtlasMind still derives specialist-provider preferences from the live refreshed model catalog first. Use overrides only when your workspace needs to pin or suppress a domain route explicitly.
